---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Merger-driven buildup of the M_BH - M_* relation - Tanaka et al. (2026)";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Merger-driven buildup of the M_BH - M_* relation bridging high-z overmassive black holes with the local relation</h1>

    <div class="infobox">
      <h3 class="infobox-title">Tanaka et al. (2026)</h3>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Type:</th>
          <td>Paper</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>First described:</th>
          <td>2026 (Tanaka et al.)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Key Papers:</th>
          <td>
            <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11747">Tanaka+2026 (arXiv:2603.11747)</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Abstract summary:</strong> Monte Carlo simulations show that merger averaging can reduce initial high-z scatter in M_BH/M_* ratios to reproduce the tight local relation; sensitivity to merger mass ratios and rates suggests observational tests at z~3-4.</p>

    <h2>Key findings</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Merger averaging can reproduce local M_BH–M_* scatter</li>
      <li>Evolution sensitive to merger mass ratios and rates</li>
      <li>Minor mergers can significantly influence scatter evolution</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li id="ref1">Tanaka, T. S., Silverman, J. D., Shimasaku, K., et al. (2026). "Merger-driven buildup of the M_BH - M_* relation." <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11747">arXiv:2603.11747</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h2>Related concepts</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/concepts/galaxy-bimodality">Galaxy bimodality</a> — merger-driven bulge/MBH growth as a quenching path</li>
      <li><a href="/concepts/black_hole_mass">Black hole mass</a> — implications for scaling relations and scatter evolution</li>
      <li><a href="/concepts/merger-driven-galaxy-evolution">Merger-driven galaxy evolution</a> (if present) — averaging effects from multiple mergers</li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</Base>
